http://www.adobe.com/privacy/policies/flash-player.html
Google Chrome App:
https://support.google.com/accounts/answer/61416?co=GENIE.Platform%3DAndroid&hl=en
These websites will also help you understand more about how Cookie-based advertising works and how you can manage your Cookie Settings:
http://www.aboutads.info/choices
http://www.youronlinechoices.eu/
Network Advertising Initiative opt-out page:
http://optout.networkadvertising.org/?c=1
We invite you to provide your images to us via social media platforms by following specific instructions such as “#yesadidas”. We will be using the images you provide for our campaign communications. We will obtain rights to your image through a licence agreement in the form of our terms and conditions. By submitting your images via social media platforms to us, you will agree for us to use your images as described in the licence agreement.
When you use the adidas app, we use push notifications in this app to communicate with you concerning the purposes stated in this Policy. This includes information that relates to purposes based on the Performance of Contract (such as your purchase). You can switch off push notifications at any time using “Settings” in your mobile devices. However, if you switch off push notifications, we may need to contact you via emails for important messages relating to your purchase.
8. HOW CAN YOU UNSUBSCRIBE FROM MARKETING MESSAGES?
You can opt out of receiving marketing messages from adidas at any time. Click ‘Unsubscribe’ at the bottom of the newsletter or marketing email that you want to unsubscribe from; or update your communication preferences in your account/app if you have one.
9. WHO IS YOUR PERSONAL INFORMATION DISCLOSED TO AND IS YOUR PERSONAL INFORMATION DISCLOSED OUTSIDE OF AUSTRALIA?
Depending on the purpose for which your Personal Information is used, your Personal Information may be shared with different third party recipients. These recipients may include:
other adidas Group entities, including the adidas Data Controllers;
third parties that provide services to us, which may include site administration support providers, IT cloud solution providers, delivery service providers, payment processing providers, payment risk solution providers, business consulting service providers, data analytics solution providers, email marketing support providers, advertising agency partners, social media platforms, targeted marketing service providers, selling partners, manufacturing providers, customer service providers and UGC support partners;
event partners;
adiClub Partners (as defined in section 7 above);
prospective buyers and investors; and
law enforcement and regulatory agencies.
Other entities in the adidas Group and some of our service providers are located outside Australia. As a result, Personal Information collected and held by us may be transferred outside Australia (including to Germany, Switzerland, the Netherlands, other countries within the European Union, the USA, the UK, Austria, Singapore, Thailand, Philippines and Malaysia). We comply with all local legal requirements to ensure your Personal Information is secured and safe when it is being transferred to a different country (including access).
10. HOW DO WE HOLD AND SECURE YOUR PERSONAL INFORMATION?
We generally hold Personal Information in computer systems, including computer systems operated for us by other adidas Group entities or our service providers.
We implement appropriate technical and organisational measures to address the risks corresponding to our use of your Personal Information, including loss, alteration, or unauthorised access to your Personal Information. We require our service providers to do the same through contractual agreements. However, you should be aware that any transmission of your Personal Information through the internet is at your own risk. We can only protect your Personal Information when we have it.
11. HOW CAN YOU ACCESS AND SEEK THE CORRECTION OF YOUR PERSONAL INFORMATION?
We take reasonable steps to ensure the personal information we collect, use and disclose is accurate, complete, up to date and relevant. You can help by letting us know about any changes to your Personal Information, such as changes to your address and phone number.
If you would like to access or correct the Personal Information adidas Australia holds about you, please contact the Privacy Officer or adidas Australia (using the contact details in section 13 below). We need to confirm your identity before we can handle your requests. When we refuse your request for legal reasons, we will tell you why.
https://www.adidas.com.au/contact.html
12. HOW CAN YOU MAKE A COMPLAINT?
Please contact the Privacy Officer (using the contact details in section 13 below) if you have any concerns or complaints about the manner in which adidas Australia has collected or handled your personal information. adidas Australia will inquire into your complaint and respond to you in writing within 30 days. If you are not satisfied with our response, you can contact us to discuss your concerns or lodge a complaint with the Australian Information Commissioner (
www.oaic.gov.au
).
13. GENERAL QUESTIONS AND SUPPORT
adidas Customer Service
ASK CUSTOMER SERVICE:
https://www.adidas.com.au/contact.html
If you have any general questions or require immediate assistance and support concerning your Personal Information, please contact:
adidas Australia Pty Limited
privacyofficer.pacific@adidas.com +61 3 9269 5221 adidas Australia Pty Limited, Level 1, 37 Dunlop Road, Mulgrave, Victoria 3170 Australia
14. UPDATES AND NOTIFICATION OF UPDATES
We review and update the Privacy Policy periodically to reflect any changes resulting from our day-to-day business operations. You can always check the date of the Privacy Policy to find out when we last made any changes.
