8. HOW CAN YOU UNSUBSCRIBE FROM MARKETING MESSAGES?
You can opt out of receiving marketing messages from adidas at any time. Click ‘Unsubscribe’ at the bottom of the newsletter or marketing email that you want to unsubscribe from; or update your communication preferences in your account/app if you have one.
9.
WHO IS YOUR PERSONAL INFORMATION DISCLOSED TO AND IS YOUR PERSONAL INFORMATION DISCLOSED OUTSIDE OF NEW ZEALAND?
Depending on the purpose for which your Personal Information is used, your Personal Information may be shared with different “Categories of Recipients”. These Recipients may include other adidas Group entities and third parties that provide services to us, including the Categories of Recipients identified in section 7 above.
Other entities in the adidas Group and some of our service providers are located outside New Zealand. As a result, Personal Information collected and held by us may be transferred outside New Zealand (including to Australia, Germany, Switzerland, the Netherlands, the USA, the UK, Austria, Singapore, Thailand and Malaysia).
10. HOW DO WE HOLD AND SECURE YOUR PERSONAL INFORMATION?
We generally hold Personal Information in computer systems, including computer systems operated for us by other adidas Group entities or our service providers.
We implement appropriate technical and organisational measures to address the risks corresponding to our use of your Personal Information, including loss, alteration, or unauthorised access to, or unauthorised disclosure of, your Personal Information. We require our service providers to do the same through contractual agreements. However, you should be aware that any transmission of your Personal Information through the internet is at your own risk. We can only protect your Personal Information when we have it.
11
. HOW CAN YOU ACCESS AND SEEK THE CORRECTION OF YOUR PERSONAL INFORMATION?
We take reasonable steps to ensure the personal information we collect, use and disclose is accurate, complete, up to date and relevant. You can help by letting us know about any changes to your Personal Information, such as changes to your address and phone number.
If you would like to access or correct the Personal Information Adidas New Zealand Limited holds about you, please contact the Data Protection Officer or Adidas New Zealand Limited (using the contact details in section 13 below). We need to confirm your identity before we can handle your requests. When we refuse your request for legal reasons, we will tell you why.
https://www.adidas.co.nz/contact.html
12.
HOW CAN YOU MAKE A COMPLAINT?
Please contact the Data Protection Officer or Adidas New Zealand Limited (using the contact details in section 13 below) if you have any concerns or complaints about the manner in which Adidas New Zealand Limited has collected or handled your personal information. Adidas New Zealand Limited will inquire into your complaint and will endeavour to respond to you in writing within 30 days. If you are not satisfied with our response, you can contact us to discuss your concerns or lodge a complaint with the Office of the Privacy Commissioner (
www.privacy.org.nz
).
