5.
What does adidas do when we transfer your Personal Data outside of Singapore?
Depending on the Personal Data processing activity, your Personal Data may be shared with different “Categories of Recipients”, who may be located outside of Singapore.
Where your personal data is transmitted outside of Singapore, such recipients may not afford a similar standard of protection as that of Singapore. However, we will take steps to ensure that such transfers comply with the requirements of applicable data protection laws.
6. How do we secure your Personal Data?
We implement appropriate technical and organisational measures to address the risks corresponding to our use of your Personal Data, including loss, alteration, or unauthorised access to your Personal Data, and empowering you to exercise your rights. We require our service providers to do the same through contractual agreements. However, you should be aware that any transmission of your Personal Data through the internet is at your own risk. We can only protect your Personal Data when we have it.
7. What are your rights and how can you exercise them?
Under the PDPA, you have the rights listed and explained below:
Get a copy of your Personal Data
You may request for a copy of your Personal Data, in accordance with your rights under the applicable data protection laws, provided that it is still within our possession or control when we receive your request. We reserve our rights to charge a reasonable fee for this request.
Access to information about your Personal Data
Subject to the provisions of and any exceptions under applicable laws, you have the right to know about the ways your Personal Data has been or may have been used by us within a year before the date of your request.
We reserve our rights to charge a reasonable fee for this request.
Make sure your Personal Data are correct
You have the right to make sure we are using accurate details about you. We shall, as required under applicable data protection laws and unless exceptions apply, send such corrected data to every other organisation to which the data was disclosed by us within a year before your request.
Withdraw your consent
When we use your Personal Data based on your consent, you have the right to change your mind and withdraw your consent at any time. We shall cease collection, use and disclosure of your Personal Data after receiving your request, unless we are otherwise permitted to do so under applicable laws. If you withdraw your consent to any and all purposes and depending on the nature of your request, we may not be in the position to continue to provide our products and services to you. Other legal consequences may also potentially arise in respect of such withdrawal, vis-à-vis your existing contracts and agreements with us.
To unsubscribe from our newsletters, click ‘Unsubscribe’ at the bottom of the newsletter or marketing email that you want to unsubscribe from; or update your communication preferences in your account if you have one.
If there are any technical issues, contact Customer Service for support.
We need to confirm your identity before we can handle your requests. When we refuse your request for legal reasons, we will tell you why.
8.
Questions, Complaints, and Support – who and how you can get in touch with us
